Network monitoring is a common IT term that is broad implication. 
Network Monitoring can refer to the pracetice, techniques, and tools used to provide insight into the status of a network. 
These techniques are used to monitor the availability and performance of network systems and troubleshoot problems. 

Some reason you may want to practice network monitoring include (But not limited to)

	1) To detect the reachablility of networked systems. 

	2) TO measure the availability of networked systems. 

	3) to determine the performance of networked systems. 

	4) To inform decisions about networked resource allocation 

	5) To aid in troubleshooting 

	6) To benchmark performance 

	7) To reverse engineer a protocal 

	8) To debug a program 
